<subSubSection id="C34D47CEFFFBC878FF0DBCDEFB53F91E" pageId="5" pageNumber="360" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BE81445FFFBC878FF0DBCDEFB53F91E" blockId="5.[151,1437,1669,2020]" pageId="5" pageNumber="360">
<emphasis id="B923C857FFFBC878FF0DBCDEFEDEF945" bold="true" box="[151,271,1669,1695]" pageId="5" pageNumber="360">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of this species can be recognised by the group of long strong anteroventral setae on the apical third of mid femur (
<figureCitation id="136C08C0FFFBC878FEADBCF2FEABF91E" box="[311,378,1705,1732]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–7" captionStartId="7.[151,262,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[450,1142,225,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[425,1163,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5–7. Drymeia fasciculata (Stein). 5. ♂ mid femur, anterior view. 6. ♀ mid femur, anterior view. 7. ♂ sternite 5, dorsal view. Scale line 0.25 mm. (Azerbaijan.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538207/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="360">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). A similar but reduced group of setae is present in the female (
<figureCitation id="136C08C0FFFBC878FBABBCF2FBA5F91E" box="[1073,1140,1705,1732]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–7" captionStartId="7.[151,262,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[450,1142,225,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[425,1163,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 5–7. Drymeia fasciculata (Stein). 5. ♂ mid femur, anterior view. 6. ♀ mid femur, anterior view. 7. ♂ sternite 5, dorsal view. Scale line 0.25 mm. (Azerbaijan.)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538207" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538207/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="360">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
